Introduction

DeVita, formerly known as Chloe DeVita is a South Korean hip-hop soloist who debuted under Jay Park's label AOMG in 2020.

Her stage name, ‘DeVita’ is derived from the movie Cinema Paradiso’s main character ‘Salvatore Di Vita’ and Argentina’s former first lady ‘Evita Peron’, representing her desire to inspire and influence listeners’ lives through her vibrantly colored music.

DeVita started gaining attention after releasing several unique and soulful tracks through SoundCloud. She has proven boundless artistic potential by collaborating with multiple artists such as Jay Park of AOMG, H1GHR MUSIC, Roc Nation and more, who has now signed her to his globally successful label.

In 2012, she appeared in the reality show "K-POP STAR" when she was 16 years old. In 2014, she participated on the show "Kollaboration Chicago" and ended up as the runner up.
